author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: Jonghyun. I want to talk about your musicality first. You possessed a talent that no other will be able to again. I love the power behind your voice. I love the way that you pronounce your words and how you choose to articulate your vocals. Your voice was so pure and thorough, and it is so evident how much passion you had for singing. You were born with a gift, with this instrument and you managed to master it and share it through various styles of songs. I love that your voice could adapt to whatever concept or style that you were met with, and you were able to diversify your lines without losing the qualities that define your voice. There was so much life behind your voice and I really believe it was the foundation of Shinee songs.  It is simply so pure and authentic, which makes it all the more honoring to be able to listen to. You were meant to be singing and warming hearts with your voice. At the same time, you were one of the most phenomenal dancers that I knew. You danced in such a way that made you stand out when executing these, while still blending in with the rest of your members. It is so easy to watch you dance because of the how naturally you moved. When you were on stage, you moved so flawlessly and so comfortably. You moved in a way that demonstrated your personal expression, but still showed all of the characteristics of Shinee’s choreographies. You paid so much attention to all of the details, and your facial expressions are included there as well. You brought Shinee’s choreographies to life and infused into them so much of your experience and professionalism as a dancer.  Overall, I hope you know how legendary of an artist you were and will always be. You are the reason we have music the way we do today, and we needed your contributions to help create its future. You will forever be modeled after and your musical persona will continue to be passed on for years to come. As much as your musicality will always be cherished, your personality will be as well, I know that nobody will hold onto it quite like your members. I can say so confidently that you have freed your members. One of the first reasons I came to figure this out is how vulnerable you have always been with them. I know you dealt with so much and felt so many conflicting emotions, and you must have seen something really valuable in your members to trust those feelings with them.  It is so evident in how close you all were because of how you’ve confided in them and believed in them since the very beginning of your time today.   Because of the time they spent with you and the way that you made them feel, they see the significance in living their lives with no fear. They look up to you because of how resilient and stable you were, all while knowing what you were dealing with. Look at all they’ve accomplished. It is simply because of the life you led that they are able to follow you and do the same. It is you who has strengthened the already unbreakable bond that you all had, and established the familial connection that you all share even further. Your members believe in each other and believe in staying together forever in order to honor you. Every action they take is in your name, and I hope you know that you could not have shown them a greater love. You are the reason they are who they are and that they can live their lives without being held back by anything. Thank you for every second that you spent showing them the greatest love imaginable. I want to personally thank your parents and family for raising you and helping you to become the talented, selfless, and inspiring man that you turned out to be. I know that they are likely the reason you were able to hold on for so long and I know that they meant the world to you. The influence they had on your life is so grand and cannot be missed.  I want to give them my condolences on behalf of all of your other loved ones, but I want to thank them more so for continuing to live out your legacy. I hope you know that you could never disappoint them and all they ever will feel for you is pride. They will always understand you and love you more than anybody else on this Earth, and they live each day continuing what you started. I thank them for continuing to honor you with all that they do; and for spreading the same generosity and love that you did. Your fans keep your family in our hearts always and forever, and will follow their lead in extending your influence in the most respectable way. On the topic of generosity, it is your fans who you likely showed the most grace to; the reason being that you always put us before yourself. You dealt with more than you ever should have, and you still made time to make sure that we were entertained and happy.  All we could have ever hoped for was you taking time that you needed, because just knowing you were there was enough for us. Just your presence was enough for us to feel comfortable and content in our own skin, but you did much more than just be there for us every day. You put in so much work just to make sure we had a piece of you to hold on to; and you never had to exert yourself just to please us. I only hope that in the time that you spent with us, you found us being as supportive as possible. I hope that you did not feel obligated to work hard for us, because as I mentioned earlier, just having you around was all we ever wanted. You put your soul into all that you did for us, and we felt it through every form of communication. You always shared how you were feeling; at least as much as you were comfortable with, and this is all more than you ever had to do. I hope that we were able to offer you at least some relief, because it was you who was saving us each and every day. There are so many fans who are who they are because of the life that you’ve shown us. I hope you don’t feel guilt because similarly to your members, you couldn’t have loved us better and shown us a better life. We could not exist without the love that you continue to show us even without being with us. We will never forget what you’ve done for us and we will continue to live our lives with you in our hearts as we live day to day. Thank you for changing our lives and helping us become who we were meant to be. I know you’ve been through a lot, both professionally and personally. What we know of is likely not even the beginning of the burdens you had to carry. I know that anybody could agree with me when I say that you are easily one of the strongest people for persevering through what you did for so long. It is the hate and the disregard for human life that drove you to make your decision, and I hope you know that we acknowledge the effect that this can have on a person. I know we will never fully understand just what you had to deal with, but we are aware of how strong you had to be to be able to stand up to it even at all. Again, this is just part of what you had to deal with, but you struggled through it with an open heart for so long. I know that facing these fears and hardships helped you to understand more about yourself and you were able to benefit from taking that leap of faith in the end. No matter if you were were a Shinee supporter or not, everybody can learn from how you decided to address what was ailing you. You have taught us not only how to interact with our problems, but also how to treat others in our lives as well. I thank you so much for putting up with what you did and for being so rigid through all of it. It is not easy to brush off those feelings, but you kept your head up for so long, and we are so beyond proud of you for the strength and resilience you’ve shown for the entirety of your life span. You teach us all with your lifestyle choices every single day. I hope you know that your loved ones are all taking this day to commemorate you and the wonderful person that you became. You had a soul too pure for this world, and today, as well as every other day, we recognize and celebrate who you were. I hope you are able to realize just how monumental and historic you are for so many people. It may be hard to view yourself in this way, but just know that your fans and family are going to celebrate your life on this very special day just for you. We will live this day exactly how you would, with nothing but love for you and others in our hearts. Thank you for sacrificing so much just to make Shinee and your own personal creations possible. Thank you for suffering through any pain, fear, anger, confusion, defeat, fear, angst, concern, worry, doubt, fatigue, and so much more just to make us happy. I want you to know we recognize each and every one of your efforts, no matter how minuscule you might think they were. Remember, that they will always change somebody’s mood, day, and life somewhere in the world. Your impact on another’s heart is just that strong. You are the reason so many people believe in themselves and are who they are today, including your members, and I hope you do’t forget that. Thank you so much for your hard work and efforts. You will always be the light in this world, and though nobody is perfect, you will forever be beautiful inside and out to your loved ones. Your love is eternal and will continue to change this world for the better. You will never be forgotten and will forever be honored and remembered! Thank you kindly, great legend, and I hope you are at peace. I hope you found happiness and bliss beyond your wildest dreams. Happy birthday Jonghyun, and we adore you so much. You will always be missed, but celebrated more fiercely! We love you.

author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: Jonghyun. I want to talk about your musicality first. You possessed a talent that no other will be able to again. I love the power behind your voice. I love the way that you pronounce your words and how you choose to articulate your vocals. Your voice was so pure and thorough, and it is so evident how much passion you had for singing. You were born with a gift, with this instrument and you managed to master it and share it through various styles of songs. I love that your voice could adapt to whatever concept or style that you were met with, and you were able to diversify your lines without losing the qualities that define your voice. There was so much life behind your voice and I really believe it was the foundation of Shinee songs.  It is simply so pure and authentic, which makes it all the more honoring to be able to listen to. You were meant to be singing and warming hearts with your voice. At the same time, you were one of the most phenomenal dancers that I knew. You danced in such a way that made you stand out when executing these, while still blending in with the rest of your members. It is so easy to watch you dance because of the how naturally you moved. When you were on stage, you moved so flawlessly and so comfortably. You moved in a way that demonstrated your personal expression, but still showed all of the characteristics of Shinee’s choreographies. You paid so much attention to all of the details, and your facial expressions are included there as well. You brought Shinee’s choreographies to life and infused into them so much of your experience and professionalism as a dancer.  Overall, I hope you know how legendary of an artist you were and will always be. You are the reason we have music the way we do today, and we needed your contributions to help create its future. You will forever be modeled after and your musical persona will continue to be passed on for years to come. As much as your musicality will always be cherished, your personality will be as well, I know that nobody will hold onto it quite like your members. I can say so confidently that you have freed your members. One of the first reasons I came to figure this out is how vulnerable you have always been with them. I know you dealt with so much and felt so many conflicting emotions, and you must have seen something really valuable in your members to trust those feelings with them.  It is so evident in how close you all were because of how you’ve confided in them and believed in them since the very beginning of your time today.   Because of the time they spent with you and the way that you made them feel, they see the significance in living their lives with no fear. They look up to you because of how resilient and stable you were, all while knowing what you were dealing with. Look at all they’ve accomplished. It is simply because of the life you led that they are able to follow you and do the same. It is you who has strengthened the already unbreakable bond that you all had, and established the familial connection that you all share even further. Your members believe in each other and believe in staying together forever in order to honor you. Every action they take is in your name, and I hope you know that you could not have shown them a greater love. You are the reason they are who they are and that they can live their lives without being held back by anything. Thank you for every second that you spent showing them the greatest love imaginable. I want to personally thank your parents and family for raising you and helping you to become the talented, selfless, and inspiring man that you turned out to be. I know that they are likely the reason you were able to hold on for so long and I know that they meant the world to you. The influence they had on your life is so grand and cannot be missed.  I want to give them my condolences on behalf of all of your other loved ones, but I want to thank them more so for continuing to live out your legacy. I hope you know that you could never disappoint them and all they ever will feel for you is pride. They will always understand you and love you more than anybody else on this Earth, and they live each day continuing what you started. I thank them for continuing to honor you with all that they do; and for spreading the same generosity and love that you did. Your fans keep your family in our hearts always and forever, and will follow their lead in extending your influence in the most respectable way. On the topic of generosity, it is your fans who you likely showed the most grace to; the reason being that you always put us before yourself. You dealt with more than you ever should have, and you still made time to make sure that we were entertained and happy.  All we could have ever hoped for was you taking time that you needed, because just knowing you were there was enough for us. Just your presence was enough for us to feel comfortable and content in our own skin, but you did much more than just be there for us every day. You put in so much work just to make sure we had a piece of you to hold on to; and you never had to exert yourself just to please us. I only hope that in the time that you spent with us, you found us being as supportive as possible. I hope that you did not feel obligated to work hard for us, because as I mentioned earlier, just having you around was all we ever wanted. You put your soul into all that you did for us, and we felt it through every form of communication. You always shared how you were feeling; at least as much as you were comfortable with, and this is all more than you ever had to do. I hope that we were able to offer you at least some relief, because it was you who was saving us each and every day. There are so many fans who are who they are because of the life that you’ve shown us. I hope you don’t feel guilt because similarly to your members, you couldn’t have loved us better and shown us a better life. We could not exist without the love that you continue to show us even without being with us. We will never forget what you’ve done for us and we will continue to live our lives with you in our hearts as we live day to day. Thank you for changing our lives and helping us become who we were meant to be. I know you’ve been through a lot, both professionally and personally. What we know of is likely not even the beginning of the burdens you had to carry. I know that anybody could agree with me when I say that you are easily one of the strongest people for persevering through what you did for so long. It is the hate and the disregard for human life that drove you to make your decision, and I hope you know that we acknowledge the effect that this can have on a person. I know we will never fully understand just what you had to deal with, but we are aware of how strong you had to be to be able to stand up to it even at all. Again, this is just part of what you had to deal with, but you struggled through it with an fighting heart for so long. I know that facing these fears and hardships helped you to understand more about yourself and you were able to benefit from taking that leap of faith in the end. No matter if you were were a Shinee supporter or not, everybody can learn from how you decided to address what was ailing you. You have taught us not only how to interact with our problems, but also how to treat others in our lives as well. I thank you so much for putting up with what you did and for being so rigid through all of it. It is not easy to brush off those feelings, but you kept your head up for so long, and we are so beyond proud of you for the strength and resilience you’ve shown for the entirety of your life span. You teach us all with your lifestyle choices every single day. I hope you know that your loved ones are all taking this day to commemorate you and the wonderful person that you became. You had a soul too pure for this world, and today, as well as every other day, we recognize and celebrate who you were. I hope you are able to realize just how monumental and historic you are for so many people. It may be hard to view yourself in this way, but just know that your fans and family are going to celebrate your life on this very special day just for you. We will live this day exactly how you would, with nothing but love for you and others in our hearts. Thank you for sacrificing so much just to make Shinee and your own personal creations possible. Thank you for suffering through any pain, fear, anger, confusion, defeat, fear, angst, concern, worry, doubt, fatigue, and so much more just to make us happy. I want you to know we recognize each and every one of your efforts, no matter how minuscule you might think they were. Remember, that they will always change somebody’s mood, day, and life somewhere in the world. Your impact on another’s heart is just that strong. You are the reason so many people believe in themselves and are who they are today, including your members, and I hope you do’t forget that. Thank you so much for your hard work and efforts. You will always be the light in this world, and though nobody is perfect, you will forever be beautiful inside and out to your loved ones. Your love is eternal and will continue to change this world for the better. You will never be forgotten and will forever be honored and remembered! Thank you kindly, great legend, and I hope you are at peace. I hope you found happiness and bliss beyond your wildest dreams. Happy birthday Jonghyun, and we adore you so much. You will always be missed, but celebrated more fiercely!! We love you.

author: @whatsup968
text:
I'm in a music appreciation class at the moment (online of course) and we do something every week so far where we take a concept we've been learning about and we find an example of it in the music we personally listen to. This week we talked about word painting/text painting, which is where something in the lyrics is shown in the music. One classic example in another song is how on the word "descending" in the lyrics the pitches descend
So for this week I just started going through all the music on my phone, just letting them play one by one to see what works, and then I hear Minho say "replay" TWICE, like he literally 'replayed' the word and pitch and everything, so now I get to talk about SHINee to my classmates :)
I'm happy to introduce them to such a bop
Haven't listened to SHINee a lot since 2017 for obvious reasons and I miss them. They were a big part of my life, so I'm happy to revisit them like this. I think I might be ready to come back to them now? I want to listen to a bunch of SHINee tonight!

author: @jjjuniper
text:
for new fans:

onew: main vocal/leader
jonghyun: main vocal
taemin: main vocal/maknae 
key: main vocal
minho: main vocal

we are called shawols, it’s short for shinee world

• they debuted may 25th 2008 and their debut song was “replay” 

• all 5 members have solo work.

taemin:
ace- the 1st mini album (2015)
press it (2016)
move (2017)
want (2019)

jonghyun:
base- the 1st mini album (2015)
story op. 1 & 2 (2015, 2017)
she is (2016)
poet | artist (2018)

key:
face (2018)
i wanna be - 1st repackaged album (2019)

onew:
voice - the 1st mini album (2018)

minho:
i’m home (single) (2019)


• jonghyun was one of the first artist in his company to have almost complete control over his creative direction and music.

• most members have done some acting, most noteworthy:

minho: 
to the beautiful you (2012)
because it’s the first time (2015)
drinking solo (cameo) (2016)
hwarang: poet warrior youth (2016)

key:
drinking solo (2016)
the guardians (2017)

onew:
descendants of the sun (2016) (love this show)

taemin: 
final life: even if you disappear tomorrow (2017)

(most of their acting work can be seen on the app viki for free)

• jonghyun wasn’t an actor but he hosted his own radio show called blue night from 2014 to 2017.

• shinee has one of the most diverse and impressive discography in their industry, they have 7 official studio albums and 5 official japanese albums.

korean albums:

the shinee world (2008)
lucifer (2010)
dream girl - misconceptions of you (2013)
why so serious- misconceptions of me (2013)
odd (2015)
1 of 1 (2016)
the story of light (2018)

japanese albums:
the first (2011)
boys meet u (2013)
im your boy (2014)
dxdxd (2016)
five (2017)

they have been nominated for various awards and jonghyun and taemin have gotten music banks number 1 song each respectively.

they have done a lot for their community, key himself alone donated to a charity right before enlisting in 2019.

there’s so much that i left out but i just wanted to lay down some basics and facts about our beloved 5 boys. if you’re new to the fandom i welcome you with warm arms and i am happy you’re here. please be good to our 5 amazing artists. they deserve all the support and love.  welcome to the shinee world <3

text:
I thought I had musical anhedonia till I was twenty. I didn't understand why people liked music. To me music was something annoying and distracting, I never ever enjoyed it.

Then suddenly, I found SHINee and for the first time music gave me everything- comfort, fun, freshness.
SHINee is so special to me- their Music is like the only music in the Universe that I really enjoy with my heart and soul. Nothing can absolutely ever replace SHINee in my life. This is how precious SHINee is to me🤗

author: @ondubu52
text: I lost my dog, she used to keep me company especially when sad, she would sit there with me and sometimes even cry when I did, as we both listened to shinee or Jonghyun. Mostly just Jonghyun when ever I was sad. But she passed. And then Jonghyun did too. I now cry for both of them alone. And often. It's so hard all by myself. It's still hard for me to listen to his voice. I wish this wasnt real. I have stopped listening to Kpop and stopped watching dramas. I've been listening and watching for longer than shinee has been around. I am 23. But they were the first group who completely snatched my heart. I just never thought they would be the ones to cause me the most pain. I love you Kim Jonghyun. But this hurts so much. I go back to that day when I first got the news early morning a lot and sometimes I relive it often and  those first 5 months were awful.. I became Ill, I couldn't sleep or eat. I would lay and cry non stop. I would go to work and burst into an uncontrollable fit of tears. I walked around without a light to follow.  Its become easier but my heart goes to that day, and those months often. I dont think itll ever stop hurting. I just hope I can one day listen to you again with a calm heart and a heart full of love again. I don't think I'll live to see the day. Kim Jonghyun I love you. ♡ you did well. I'm so sorry.

author: @foortunecookie_
text: this is one of my fave song by Shinee, and finally after one year I'm able to listen to it again and I'm crying so hard right now..I don't think I will ever accept this..of course sometimes Jonghyun seemed to be sad, he talked about mental illness a lot but I still don't understand it..most of the times he looked so happy, he had loving family, 4 brothers and milion of fans who love him..this is so hard for me, it makes me so sad that we will never hear new Shinee song with all of them..I respest Minho, Key, Onew and Taemin so much that they decided to comeback, I love their new album so much but it's not the same without Jonghyun and never will be..his voice was one of kind, and without him something is missing..seeing his beautiful smile in this mv breaks my heart into a milion pieces, I wish he will be still with us and I can take at least half of his pain away..thinking how he suffered before he leaved us..ending your life is not the way! life is beautiful, I bet there are many people who loves us, we still have so many things to do and to see, there is always way to get out of problems..sometimes I wish I would not love Shinee and their music this much because now I will be less hurt and not crying that many times :(

text:
I only discovered this group yesterday and already have loaded my phone with lots of they're songs. especially they're solos (Jonghyun and Taemin). I'm very sorry for Jonghyun not only for his talent but also as a human being who struggled a lot in his life till that point. i wish could have found the strength to endure a little more, but in the end, that's life and we are just human beings with all the strengths and weaknesses we get. I really hope that now he can rest in peace and wish for his family and friends to live in peace with his joyful memories. 
regarding this song, I'm curious to know how come Onew only sings sitting and never dances. did anything happen to him at that time? BTW his voice is amazing :D

author: @stevepark5165
text: I don't want to do this anymore. It hurts so bad I just can't do it. When Jonghyun left, I wanted to leave too. I would never end my life, but I just want the pain to stop. But all I have is pain. I try to accept them as a group with 4 members, but my heart can't let go of Jonghyun. I don't talk with anyone about how I feel because I just feel weak if I do. I don't want to talk about my problems. I just miss Jonghyun so much I don't know what to do anymore. I need strength when I feel this way, but all I can do is cry in my room at night in the dark, silencing my sobs. I'm just tired of this. My step dad also passed away in September and I just can't handle the pain from that too. I feel like so many people I love and care about are dying. What do I do?

author: @kiararose8896
text:
For anyone new to SHINee because despite Jonghyun’s passing, it is never to late to join the fandom. 
Fandom name: Shawols
Fandom Color: Pearl Aqua Green 
Debut: May 25, 2008 
Members:

0:22 Lee Jinki (Onew) Leader, oldest, lead singer, known for his smooth, stable and deeper vocals. Very sweet and funny guy. 

0:32 Kim Jonghyun: main singer, dancer. He is known for his high vocals, being a poet & artist and for his soft puppy dog eyes. He had a solo career and made 5 albums. He was a very sentimental, smart, fun, and loving person who was talented in everything. 

0:16 Kim KiBum (Key): singer, rapper, 2nd best dancer and actor. He speaks English because he lived in America. He loves fashion and is a little more flamboyant and sassy. He’s a sweetheart and you can follow him on his instagram: bumkeyk 

1:16 Choi Minho: main rapper, dancer, and vocals. He is known as flaming charisma as he is very outgoing, funny, athletic, and kind. He is a great actor as well. 

0:03 Lee Taemin: Maknae, Main dancer, singer, & solo artist. He debuted as a dancer at the age of 15 and was called “tone deaf.” Now he has an amazing solo career and is known as the “Korean Michael Jackson.”

Edit: Thanks for correcting me. Its been a while since Ive came back to this mv.

author: @FELIXB3
text: I've been seeing mainly from people who only recently joined the fandom bcuz Jong died or after he died they became more interested in only him for whatever personal reason. But people saying Shawols didnt care about him or we didnt try to help him or we treated him badly. I need to set the record if you find one fandom that cares deeply about each member its this one. We knew Jong had depression it was no mystery we tried to uplift him with positive comments & feed back & keep him protected from antis. Jong's depression just happened to be severe that he probably needed someone physical & not just online comments to lift his spirits. Do not come into this fandom telling us we caused his depression or we never loved him. I assure you we loved him & we love all of SHINee so much & only want to give them the world.

author: @수리-d4q
text:
우릴 위해서 무대에서 웃어주기만했던 종현아,넌 정말 봄보다 어느누구보다 따뜻했던 사람이었어.음,비록 우리는 너에게 따뜻한 존재가 되어주지못해서 정말 미안해.그리고 내가 너한테 할수 있는말이  미안해밖에없어서 정말 더 미안해 ...나는 너가 하늘에서 이쁘게,멋지게 노래부르고 있을꺼라고 생각할께...아쉽게도 2018년의 봄을 너랑 같이 보지는,느끼지는 못하겠지만  너는 지금쯤 더 따뜻한 너의 봄을 느끼고 있겠지?너의 안타까운 선택을 우리가 뭐라 할 자격은없어..잘했다고도 못했다고도..하지만 지금은 우리다 너의 선택을 원망하지않을려도 그러고 있는게 당연한거겠지?너의 무대는 너란 존재는 많은 사람의 마음을 울리고 녹여줬던것 같아...빛이나 너는..그걸 블링블링이라고 표현조차 할수 없을만큼...근데 지구에서 아름답게  빛이나던게 하늘로가 더 빛이나는 우리의 별이 됬다는게 너무 슬프다..지금은 내가 널 위해 할수있는게 울어주는거인것 같아..너가 우는 우리의 모습을 보며 너가 얼마나 훌륭하고 완벽했었는지 알아줬음 좋겠어!하루하루가 지나고,시간은 흘러가네..당연한거지..하지만 우리는 절대 널 잊지않아.영원히 기억할꺼야..우리의 마음속에서 빛날꺼야..너무고맙고 또 고맙다 너란 존재를 볼수 있었던게, 목소리를 들을수 있었던게,너의 무대를 봤다는게.....왜 난 시간이 가면 갈수록 더 슬퍼지고 널 좋아하게 되는걸까...
그동안 너무 수고했고 고생했어..사랑해 종현아 정말 수고했어....정말로 ...우리 나중에 꼭  보자,만나자!

author: @notclg
text:
Last week I was starting to get into Shinee, I mean really getting into them, I've been so obssesed with them lately. The day before Jonghyun passed away I remember I couldn't stop listening all of their songs while working. I guess I wanted to become a Shawol so bad, watching their videos, falling in love with each one of them, specially Key and Jonghyun for some reason. Then the next day I read the news and I just couldn't believe it, I couldn't hold tears, I'm so freaking sad right now. I don't even feel I deserve to become a Shawol now. I mean, I feel It's too late. Almost 10 years without supporting them, supporting Jonghyun.. I don't know what to do now. The rest of the members must feel terrible, and I can't do nothing, I can't pretend I've been a Shawol for so long and say I love them so much because I wasn't one when the 5 were together. I wish so much I could've noticed their music and talent at least 1 year ago, and not 2 months ago... I wasn't even into kpop the first months of 2016... All I can say to the members, his family and fans is to please, Stay strong. 
Shawols, you deserve the whole world for supporting this amazing and talented group until now, including the smile of a beautiful boy which I missed in its best moments and I hate myself for that. You need to know how lucky you all are to have lived that at the right time.
Jonghyun you can rest in peace now. I swear I'll listen to all of your songs and appreciate the talented and bright man you really was, that's the only thing you deserve and the only thing I can do now...

I love seeing how much fun they were having but can't help thinking of what was going on in his head during this time. 
BUT STILL I SHOULDNT BE SAD. This is a time for all of us to be together and keep each other strong. Let's continue to celebrate Jjong's life together! ❤️

text: I can remember the moment exactly that I fell in love with Jonghyun. It was in March of this year when me and my cousin were on the way to SHINee's concert in Dallas. She biased Jonghyun, I biased Minho, but she insisted on having me bias Jonghyun as well. So, she started playing all of his solo songs. It was after that car ride and seeing them live, that I really fell in love with him. His songs were brilliant, he was a genius, and just something about him made him REALLY stand out. He was so special. SHINee has always been THAT group that I consider unique to my heart. I can't tell you how much I love them... my hear hurts, and it will probably continue hurting... but I have peace of mind knowing that Jonghyun is at peace, wherever he is.

author: @anhanh5528
text: I hate to deal with the fact that these songs would never be the same anymore. Not only because our beloved Jonghyun's not here with us, but also because it can never feel the same anymore. Through the past few days, I've listened to SHINee over and over and over again and realized such energetic and enthusiastic songs could ever be this sad. When I scroll down to see the comments, I always expect to see positive and loved comments about the songs and the bands. And now it'll never come usual again. We will never only talk about how Key is so handsome, Taemin is so cute in that hairstyle, Minho needs more lines, Onew's voice is so warm and Jonghuyn is killing those high notes as well as dance moves. Instead, all we feel and want to express is our pain, our recall, our late encouragement. I wish all this stuff is just a bad nightmare and when we wake up tomorrow and open Replay, Lucifer, Ring Ding Dong, Hello,... It's only about how cool they are and maybe a little debate about Jonghyunie and Lil Taemin who's the handsom-er between two fangirls. I'm sorry I can't think straight to write something better.  😭😭😭😭😭😭 Just still can't believe that he's gone...

author: @2kool4u78
text: I bought the album that this was featured on today because I needed something to help me cope.  I went to the store to try and buy something Jonghyun related and when I got there almost everything was gone (which I expected because of what happened).  I asked if they happened to have any more merchandise and luckily they still had two albums left.  I decided to buy the album since I wanted something, though I was disappointed that I could not get Jonghyun's album.  Though when I got to the car I opened the album and found that it had Jonghyun's photo card.  I immediately broke down because I felt happy that in the end I was able to have something to remember him by, but also because the situation still really upsets me.  Anyway, I feel he was looking out for me when I picked that album.  Like he was letting me have a piece of him without me expecting it.  I just wanted to share my experience.  Thank you Jonghyun.  Rest in peace, you did well

author: @chevelle921
text:
To be honest, it's been three days and the news didn't feel real to me but after watching this MV again it kind of hit me that we'll never be able to see our Jonghyun perform this or any other SHINee song with the other members and the thought of it hurts so bad. Jonghyun, I'm sorry that you felt this way, I'm sorry that there was nothing anyone could do to help you but we will never forget you and we will carry on legacy and continue to support SHINee as OT5. I love you so much, my bias and now my angel. 

And to fellow Shawol's, Jonghyun fans or simply anyone who's been affected, just know that there is always someone to talk to, whether it be a friend on the internet or even a stranger, there is always someone willing to listen and help. Stay Strong and keep your heads up <3

text: I've never been the biggest Shawol, but it's very tragic and my feelings goes out to all the kpop fandoms out there. This is another reminder to cherish and love all the members and solo artists to the fullest everyday. We take their kindness, cheerfulness, and selflessness for granted. We need to stop pointing out every single flaw or imperfections they have. This may sound really redundant and repetitive, but we need to spread more love, especially in the kpop community, because it's so toxic lately with all those fan wars.

author: @evelynkerstein1077
text:
JONGHYUN I MISS YOU










Seriously. I never was a big Shinee fan, I don't even know that much about kpop. All I know is that you were my favorite. My cousin showed me a bunch of Shinee songs (This one is my favorite), and a bunch of Shinee comedy. I picked Jonghyun as my bias mainly because I liked his character and his personality in one of the comedy videos I watched of Shinee (I believe it was Over Flowers??) Anyways, you will be deeply missed. I am so sorry about how you felt, know that you NEVER have to be ashamed of who you love, and who your attracted to. I hope you are in peace, you are happy, and you are proud of all the hard work you have done in your life and all of your great accomplishments. We all miss you, rest in peace Jonghyun.

author: @annekalland5840
text:
I know that many of you are really sad now, I am too. I just think we need to move on sometime. Because one of the reasons Jonghyun committed suicide was because of stress. And if he was alive now if would have been stress for him. So all of you fans out there I think we just have to move on and try to do the best out of it. Like he sacrificed him self to give us a hint that we have to open our eyes and do something with this. If he suffered like this I can promise you that other artists also do. 

So this is what I recommend you to do; 
- If you have a friend that suffers, THEN HELP HIM/HER! Not just watch. Even if it is just a little thing then, it can end like it did with Jonghyun.
- This one is to all managers out there. Stop treating them like they are an animal. THEY ARE HUMANS JUST LIKE US! A HUMAN CAN NOT STAND THAT MUCH STRESS!

Take this as a hint to become better. Try to find the positive sides with it. Even if it looks just like a deep, endless hole then. There is always some positive sides with it

R.I.P. JONGHYUN❤️❤️

author: @mymisteriu172
text:
I'm going to be leaving this note everywhere I can. Today is 12.18.2017, also known as the death date of the beloved Kim Jonghyun. I want this message to get to everyone:

I don't care if you stanned Jonghyun, if he was your bias, if you didn't even know him, I don't want your sympathy. We don't need you empathy. 

"I don't stan SHINee, but I just want to be there for the people who loved Jonghyun and SHINee."

"Why would he do this? He had everything and he lead a good life?"

"Why would you do this?! We loved you!"

Let me get this straight. JONGHYUN is not just an idol, NOT just a celebrity, NOT just a role model, NOT just a member of SHINee, he was also a freaking HUMAN. AND BEFORE YOU ALL go out there throwing out all your sympathy and sorrowness, I just want to say before you do all of that please understand. Please understand that Jonghyun was a human with emotions. Please understand that he suffered to. And like me, do not judge a book by its covers. It was obvious through eyes, he was happy, we THOUGHT that he was happy. Please don't bury him with words. You know what's upsetting though? There are fans in the comments like "Why would you do this to us? We loved you!" They're blaming him for taking his own life and making themselves look like the victims. It's so annoying, I get that they miss him, but he doesn't owe anything to them. I wish they would just let him rest in piece. He obviously thought it through before doing it. You know he even rented out a place in order to do it, he really did thought it through. 

And the other comments, "He was loved, why would he take his life?" WHAT YOU SEE ON THE OUTSIDE CAN BE COMPLETELY DIFFERENT FROM WHAT"S ON THE INSIDE. Also, "What could have happened to make him take his own life?" HONEY, HAVE YOU HEARD OF DEPRESSION.

*AND DO YOU KNOW WHAT AN ANGEL HE IS.* HE'S  DONATING HIS ORGANS AND LEAVING HIS *INHERITANCE TO HIS SISTER*

And if you ever see those people like I have, "Y'all go spam "Oof" and roast the people on there. (Jonghyun's instagram). This KPOP singer who committed suicide and it's funny triggering their fans.": PLease do not let these people get their fun annoyuing you, mocking Jonghyun's death. Ignore them, repot them, do not pick a fight like they are. You know why? It's because we are not them, we DO NOT MOCK ONE"S DEATH. We are called human for a reason and it's time we start acting like them.

I hope you all understand the main issue. Ignore hte fact that he was famous, an idol, he had skin and bones like all of us. He has a heart. Don't go asking why and go support. Support those who are struggling. TAKE THIS AS A WAKE UP CALL. 

Jonghyun deserved more.

author: @gracerobinson11
text:
I know I'm not the only one saying this, but here's another voice.
Dear, jonghyun
We love you. We knew about your depression....now idk if SM did anything. We all knew you were depressed, but I don't think to the extreme. It saddens me that you were in so much pain. It was obvious in your eyes (maybe it's just a reflection of how I feel idk) but you sing and smile with such passion it was easy to pass off. We don't know the pain you went through...we will never understand just how painful living was for you...you thought death was the best option...and that's sad. We all understand...it wasn't your fault...something (or many thing) pushed you over the edge... I just hope you can sing your heart out in heaven...we'll all continue to support SHINee even if they disband. For many of us, you guys were our introduction to kpop, myself included. I hope you're not disappointed in yourself. You shouldn't be. None of us are mad, and if we are, we're mad at the world, not you. Keep singing up in heaven... you deserve peace...again we love you so much...you will be absolutely missed.
Love, myself and probably many Shawols.

To my fellow Shawols and other fandoms,
We will continue to support SHINee...we all need to be supported and support each other. We're all grieving, we're all shocked. Maybe there was something we could have collectively done, I don't know. But what I do know, jonghyun loved us. He loved music. He loved producing music for us and everyone. While we may never understand why, we need to collectively understand that he didn't want to live. That life was far too painful for him. I hate to say it (I mean he was my bias so this is especially hard) but we need to forgive. I understand your probably going to be mad, and that's okay. I will be right beside you in that anger. But we can't get mad at jonghyun. He wasn't in the right state of mind and unfortunately that state of mind, took him away. We need to be gentle to not only ourselves, but each other and especially the other members of SHINee. I'm sure you may want to blame the others. I will too, but they aren't at fault. They didn't see through the smiling sunshine. Really hardly anyone of us did. The only thing we can blame, is time. Time took him away. So just be gentle. We'll all be on edge and very sad. So please if your depressed and even contemplating suicide, back away from the news, log off of everything, all social media and just take time to be with family and friends. Tell them you love them. Reach out to suicide hotlines, if you are considering suicide. And if you are, believe me and remember this. Suicide may end your pain, but it's a life time sadness for your friends and family. I love you all. I loved being part of this fandom. So many jokes. So much laughter. Let's keep it that way and still have fun (again even if they disband) let's support taemin and the others if they decide to go solo. They may also decide to stay together and if they do, we'll support them.
One last thing,  jonghyun isn't gone. He's with all of us. And I feel like he was with every single one of us today. He didn't want to hurt us. He wanted to find peace for himself. He'll be watching us until we're past the five stages. Again I love you all. 
Your fellow Shawol, CS
Side note, jonghyun, I pray you have found peace and I pray that your going to be doing your shows up in heaven.

This is too much for me to take. I saw him for the first time many many years on hello baby. I loved him most then because the streak of yellow in his hair stood out to me and his love for the baby was heart warming. So i stuck close with him and always had deep respect for shinee. I was so excited when I saw the Night Goblin preview of Jonghyun with Nu'est JR. Thought how cute he looks. I never would have expected this. I am so lost right now, this doesnt even feel like real life.

Kim Jonghyun was one of the few people in this industry who stood up for what he believed in no matter what the backlash. He openly supported the LGBT+ community and talked openly about mental health, he was critisized for both. A beautiful man, with one of the best voices this industry will ever know. One of the kindest hearts this world will ever know. Kim Jonghyun is a legend that will never be forgotten for his humanity and talent.

Kim Jonghyun will be loved eternally. Today the world gained an angel. Rest in Peace my sweet Prince.

I love you. Always and forever.

Today I'm thinking about how I attempted suicide 4 times and how SHINee was by my side every time I didn't success.

Today I'm sending all my prayers and all my courage for people who truly love him for who he is. 

I love you Jonghyun, please be safe in Heaven. Rest in peace dear jjong.
Shawols, friends and family, be safe, ask for help and stay fucking strong. 

If you guys need help, my DM on Twitter are open @ChoiTaeni .

- a multi fandom stan who listen to kpop since 2006 and grew up with groups as SHINee who saved multiple times her suicidal's ass.

author: @134sophiek
text: To all of the other fandoms, thank you. Shawols really appreciate your support and your respect to Jonghyun and his memory. SHINee haven't lost a member, they've gained an angel. We are in mourning right now and I know that I'm in the stage of denial. Which is why I have a favour to ask all of you, all of you reading this, please whoever you love, whatever group you Stan, please go and tell your idols you love them. Jonghyun spoke often about his struggles, in his songs, interviews and in general. He was very open about it. Unfortunately Korea isn't very open on mental health issues, but I hope now they are. Jonghyuns death has come as a shock to all of us, I really shouldn't be saying anything because my heart is broken, but I feel it's important. Even the industry seems shocked as a lot of other idols are paying condolences and canceling schedules. Even Ex- EXO members Luhan and Tao have given condolences, that just shows how much of an impact Jonghyun had. He was a true inspiration to many, but it seems he didn't know it. In many conversations it seems like Jonghyun didn't feel he was good enough, he didn't feel he was doing enough. He seemed to not only have depression, but a bit of a lack of confidence in himself. I wish as a Shawol I would of told him more often how much I love him, how talented he is and to be strong, how much he meant to so many people, how much we all appreciated him and that he is amazing. Jonghyun believed in a lot of things and stood up for people of all kinds. SHINee as a whole are a very respected group, but Jonghyun as an artist was truly magnificent. Jonghyun talked about his troubles because he wanted to change things, he wanted to bring awareness to it. I feel like as a Shawol, I failed him, I couldn't save him. I should of told him I love him and made it better. This is a heartache Shawols are going to have to deal with. But, if one thing can come from this, it's change. His legacy can live on and in respect of his memory we can change things. Idols are humans, they have struggles they make mistakes, please start identifying this. Stop the fanwars, stop the hate and the trolls and the antis. Everything, just stop. We need to start helping these idols, we need to start respecting them and what they go through. Their lives are the most important thing, over all else. If your idols are sad, please try and cheer them up. If they tell you they are it's because they trust you and they're looking for your support, please give it to them. If they need to take a break, please understand and wait for them. You can wait for them. There is no time longer than forever and we've lost Jonghyun forever, so please wait for your idols. Please people of other fandoms, when idols get into scandals, be careful of your words, don't jump to conclusions and hate, they're  still human and they make mistakes, your words can not only affect them, but the people who love them to. Shawols have been trying to support OT5 the best we could because they're a family. But all this time, the media and antis kept trying to tear SHINee apart, not noticing Jonghyun suffering behind it all, that should of mattered. SHINee was important to Jonghyun, his members were like family. Jonghyun isn't the first idol to go through this, I thought T.O.P would of been a lesson to people about treating idols better, luckily he survived but his near death experience should of taught people that they're humans to, but it didn't. Things stayed the same, got worse even and now we've lost our Jonghyun forever. This is real, he's really gone. We can't bring him back, but his death can mean something. His legacy can carry on so that he doesn't die in vain. Please, respect the idols as humans, care for them, have an understanding for them. Whoever is reading this, if you're a multifandom or one group only, it doesn't matter. Go and tell your idols that you love them, go and tell them they're important and they're amazing and they mean everything to you. Tell them that you're there for them, that you support them. Make them feel loved and appreciated. Because we can't tell Jonghyun these things anymore. You can change things, you can help your idols, you can protect them. Jonghyun is our guardian angel now, he looks down upon SHINee, he will protect them. His life had so much purpose and he deserved so much better. I don't know what will happen with SHINee now, but they will always be OT5, Jonghyun will not be forgotten. I hope the industry learns to help and support their idols better and learns that mental health issues are real and I hope that all of you appreciate your idols and care for them. Because you should and because you can. We can't tell Jonghyun we love him, but you can still tell your idols that you love them. Every idol is important to their fans and to their groups, SHINee have lost Jonghyun in the worst possible way. So please, appreciate your idols, appreciate that they're with you. No matter how big or small their problems seem, care for them and protect them. Shawols have been wishing to see OT5 to stand on stage together again for so long and now we never will again. One of my biggest dreams was to see SHINee perform and to meet them. I knew Jonghyun was a kind soul and I wanted to meet him and tell him how special he is. I'll never get the chance now. Shawols that have met him or had the chance to see him sing live, please cherish these memories and all of us can cherish the memory of him. Everyone else please cherish your idols and the time you still have with them. But all of us, please let Jonghyuns death serve as much of a purpose as his life did, let's all remember him for who he was. Jonghyun our sweet angel, I miss you now and I will forever. You will always remain in our hearts and we will always love you. SHINee are always going to be five and you will always be with us. Sleep easy my love, you'll be okay now. 💙💙

author: @suzuka3785
text:
Jonghyun, notre merveilleux Jonghyun. 

Vingt-sept années d’existence sur notre horrible planète bleue. Il t’en a fallu du courage, pour arriver jusque-là… Si tu savais comme je t’en suis reconnaissante, d’avoir essayé de vivre. Tu étais ce genre de gars splendide, qui, à chaque fois que la vie lui jouait un mauvais tour, se relevait toujours, la tête haute. Je crois Jonghyun, que tu n’avais pas conscience de l’être exceptionnelle que tu représentais. Ce type de personne si rare, capable de mettre ses problèmes de côté pour arranger ceux des autres. Tu étais si unique. Pour être honnête, tu m’as sauvé plusieurs fois du précipice, de la noyade ; tu étais celui qui me faisait rire gorge la déployée, qui me faisait sourire à en avoir mal aux joues, quand tout allait mal dans mon quotidien. Parce que c’est ça, c’est tout à fait ça, tu étais le Soleil lui-même, capable d’éclairer de bonheur de générations entières. 

Pour avoir rendu ma vie meilleure, pour m’avoir offert un espoir, je te remercie, je crie, j’hurle, je pleure ma reconnaissance infinie.

Et aussi, je suis désolée. Désolée d’avoir été impuissante face à tes souffrances. Désolée de n’être qu’une fille inutile, incapable de rendre l’espoir que tu m’as jadis accordé. Désolée de n’être que « cette fan » parmi tant d’autres. Désolée que tu aies dû dissimuler ta vraie personnalité, tes véritables sentiments toutes ces années pour ne pas inquiéter. 

Tu t’es suicidé. 

Tu ne trouvais pas ta place dans ce pauvre monde. Et diable, qu’est-ce que je te comprends, je connais cette sensation par cœur, moi aussi. Alors, maintenant que tu en as l’opportunité, libère-toi de tes maux, envole-toi dans le vent, profite de cette délivrance. Je souhaite de tout mon cœur que ton âme trouve la paix intérieure.

Courage aux collègues, à la famille, à tous les proches de Kim Jonghyun. Courage à Taemin, Key, Onew et Minho, qui ont perdu bien plus qu’un membre de SHINee, bien plus qu’un frère de cœur, aujourd’hui. Courage à toutes les Shawols, qui comme moi, sentent leur monde se détruire. 

Kim Jonghyun, notre merveilleux Kim Jonghyun, notre petite légende. Nous ne t’oublierons jamais. Jamais, jamais, jamais. 


Je t’aimais comme je t’aimerais toujours.

Thank you for everything, Jonghyun. You brought so much joy to many lives through your music and your vibrant self and I can't thank you enough. Though I wish you hadn't gone this way, I hope you are at peace.

author: @user-uu5dc6wr6h
text:
He's an artist that will always remain in my memory, especially from when I was 11 to 17 and onforth. Jonghyun has contributed so much to my adolescence but I know he'll stay onto my adulthood, too.

He was an artist that was unafraid to express his genuine thoughts, his androgyny, and his opinions. He is the first man I've really seen be so open to showing his emotions and was so encouraging of others to do the same. He was talented beyond measure both in terms of singing and in writing. He was loving and so caring. Shawols were always grateful for his kindness to his fans, to the closeness he allowed. He was accepting and respectful of everyone.

As an artist and an idol, he made his family, his members, and his fans so happy. He worked his way out of poverty and made his family so happy, something only some achieve. He has made so many songs that I'll be listening to forever. I know that he's touched a lot of people through his music.

No matter what, I'm so grateful that I knew that Kim Jonghyun existed and that I lived in the same time he did. And I'm so grateful that people after his time, after our time, will be able to see the marks he's left and feel sad that they weren't as lucky as us.

He was beautiful in so many ways. He'll really never be forgotten now. The world lost a really amazing person today.
Kim Jonghyun, I love you. We love you.

author: @abbyrichmond8123
text:
And just like that my life has been turned upside down. My first ever Kpop bias. Gone. Jonghyun, words cannot describe how much you will be missed by the Kpop community, especially myself. You made me smile more times than I can count and I just wish that if you could have just smiled once more how differently this night could have turned out to be.  
Well, you're where you belong now anyway...with the angels. and I know we will still be able to hear your angelic voice if not even better than before. 
You meant so much to me and millions of other people and I just hope you know that your energy will live on for the many years to come. 
My heart goes out to Jonghyun's family, friends, SHINee and most definitely the rest of us Shawols. We don't have to suffer alone. If you need someone to talk to, I'm here, reach out to other Shawols too. We lost a beautiful soul but I know together with SHINee we will still stand brave.
I've had to reread this several times because what good is it when you can't see through a mass of tears?...

Fly high 김종현.

사랑합니다  

~A Shawol

author: @halogen5076
text:
For the interested : this music genre is called New Jack Swing. This is a fusion between hip hop music, funk and R&B. Famous timeless artists would be Michael and Janet Jackson,  Teddy Riley, SWV, Ralph Tresvant, TLC, Jade, Bobby Brown, Keith Sweet and it goes on...
However, New Jack Swing has a very little audience nowadays so you won't find a lot of artists out there. Fortunately, some of them are still part of the industry and have an incredible amount of talent. Just take a look at Bell Biv DeVoe's last album and Bruno Mars's "24K Magic" album, you won't be disappointed. :)

Oh by the way, I'm really glad I found this song. It really stands out from the tons of generic kpop songs we have at the moment. I hope they'll shine brighter in a near future!

author: @thepridefulones5883
text:
Hi, I have one thing to say, SHINee is the best, 

Onew, you never fail to impress me with your strange sense of humor and beautiful melodious voice that flows so smoothly, your smile always makes my heart skip a beat and the way that you handle this group of hooligans so ell never ceases to amaze me.

Jonghyun, you always capture my heart with your gorgeous voice that seems like it can hit any note, you sing with such a passion I also really admire you for trying to help the gays in Korea, and you are always going to stay in my heart.
Key, oh god, you truly are the almighty key, you excels at everything, and that fashion sense of yours never stops impressing me, your sassy laid back attitude is absolutely priceless, but I love hen you let your caring side show.

Minho, flaming charisma Minho, Minho dibidibidis, your are something else entirely, from your rapping to your acting you never falter, you never give up, your strong personality and you in general are just something to be admired.

Taemin, Taeminnie, Tae Tae, Taemint, my beautiful, sexy, handsome dancing machine, my god… you always approach everything with a smile on your face, you are extremely determined, you are such a handsome (or as you like to say, sexy) wonderful, kind, young man. When you move I can’t tear my eyes away from the screen, your body moves to the beat in perfect harmony and you shine with the light of billions of stars when you dance. Your voice is also another thing to be admired, you have such a smooth voice, like a stream gently moving along, you sing with such a passion and with such charisma on stage. You are somebody to be admired, I have yet to see a dancer who moves the way that you do and I honestly doubt that ever will be. You have stolen the hearts of millions of fans with the simplest smile. Everything about you, from your strong funny caring personality, to your cutest aeygo. (If you couldn’t tell already he’s my bias)
 
 I am very sad to say goodbye, I have decided to end this life of mine on the early side, I am rather young fan and I don’t want to continue anymore. This is going to sound very selfish but could you try and bring this comment their attention? I want to let them know that they inspired me in the best way possible. Please comment on this and tell them how they inspired you or made your day better!
-Goodbye forever

author: @sophiek134
text: I don't know if anyone is still here, but there's something I need to talk about. If any of you have seen Jonghyuns "She is" comment section, you will understand this. In that comment section there seems to be a load of trolls (I hope they are) saying bad things about SHINee and Shawols and even Jonghyun. The way they talk about him is awful. But they also hate on Taemin because he gets more attention from SM. However, they are making a point that Shawols don't care about Jonghyun, however I know we do, but we care for him as SHINees Jonghyun. I've noticed a lack of Shawols on Jonghyuns MVs and I really feel like we need to support his solos more. I've been spending my time trying to defend Shawols to those awful people because I know we all love and appreciate Jonghyun, Shawols are an amazing fandom. But I can't help but notice how few are there. Please Shawols, I ask you, go to Jonghyuns Lonely mv and leave a loving comment. Tell him how much you love and appreciate him. We need to work harder for him because he does so much for us. So I ask of you to show these haters that we Shawols do love Jonghyun. So let's show him lots of support. Please 😊

text: I can't believe people think that views matter so much. I don't care if this MV didn't get many views but that doesn't mean SHINee isn't famous anymore. PSY has the most watched video of all time on YouTube but does that mean he's better than artists like Michael Jackson whose song Billie Jean has around 400M on YouTube? It's the influence that matters the most. SHINee is one of the main groups that spread Kpop around the world. Back when even 20M was a lot for a Kpop song they got a lot of views. Even if this song didn't get a lot of views their album sales are still pretty good and they're highly successful in Asia. Remember that YouTube isn't the main streaming website in every country. For example in China YouTube is banned. If YouTube was available in China I'm pretty sure many Kpop and pop music videos would have been watched more. Nowadays I see many Kpop fans(especially Armies) trying to increase the views of their favourite Kpop group and act as if they're the best Kpop group ever. I'm not offending anyone but I'm just so sick of these so called 'Kpop fans' who think views matter the most and push other groups behind. Ps. I mean some armies. I love BTS too but I've gotten sick of the fandom. Not every Army is like this but there are many who give a bad name to the fandom.

author: @jwyz26
text: Aren't they literally the best kpop boy group out there today? It's understandable that they aren't as popular as they used to be back when kpop wasn't all overused boring American pop music and new groups with literally the same old concepts. Shinee have always been so original and yes that's a factor as to why they're not as big in the industry as they used to be. I mean they are still REALLY big but just not as talked about which is basically what happens to all senior groups unless you're a group like Big Bang where even after 10 years everyone loves you the same. I mean yeah shinee don't get too good promotions and even though shawols is a hUGE fan base its just that most of us are older and less active fans. Probably older kpop fans who've stanned them since debut but are now in Uni or have jobs? I mean personally no I'm still a teen in high school and only properly stanned them this year after years of my sister showing me vids of them but me not giving a shit and saying they looked like girls (¿?) bc I was a strange tween???? Shinee are pretty rich, successful and known and have a fan base that adore the shit out of them so what more could they want? They're humble, down to earth and talented men and I really hope we get to see more of them. It's sad that the industry doesn't talk about originality in groups like shinee as much as the same old boring overused group concepts. Oh well. That's modern pop for us.

author: @anumnazahah5508
text:
I had to stop everything I was doing to write this comment. (Anyways, I am not gonna comment abt the visuals bcs the MV director really wants us to appreciate the sound and also bcs the visual & dancing is a+). okay here we go:
1. This is such a perfect song. Listen to how it was structured. kudos to the composer and also the lyricist. the song came off as 'light' but I am absolutely sure they put really careful thoughts into every beats and sound.
2. The lines are fairly distributed, each member serves their purpose.
3. I was listening to this song in highest quality on spotify and noticed the harmonies and adlibs and they are incredible (pay attention to the vocal layers). The sense they put in singing each lines worth every compliments.
4. This song is the most-shinee song ever even though it isnt as bold as Married to The Music (which was an absolute masterpiece).
5. I hope that shinee will continue making music bcs they are serious in putting out good music.

I hope that everyone involved in making this song receives the compliments they deserve. 수고하셨습니다.

author: @kachan1457
text:
Honestly when I think of 1of1 Im really proud, but then when I go to youtube I just get sad, not because of the views but because of all the people talking about it. It's like we've become so used to "if the view count is low, they're unpopular" like NO. I LOVE SHINEE, and in korea they are doing AMAZING, bare in mind that they promoted with BTS, which is like a group with a major fanbase. SHINee has been in the industry for 8years now, so of course they arent THAT popular anymore, but they are still doing REALLY well, despote the fact that SM BARELY promotes them, AND THAT THEY PARTICIPATE IN COMPOSING AND WRITING LYRICS.
Like which other group, that has a major fanbase, does this? Most of them get the hit songs, learn the choreo and lyrics, get awesome promotion and BAM, 40M views. SHINee is different, but I can apreciate that, because for me it doesn't matter. I dont look at the views, I read the comments and I want to see how my babys are being praised by fans, but instead I see everyone sad because of the views..

author: @CaithlinPena
text:
Dear Shawols, you've probably all noticed the amount of trolls picking on our boys and on our fandom as well. Don't retaliate, don't feed them, and just ignore them. We're known as one of K-pop's most peaceful fandom, and we don't want to ruin that name, because what we do reflects on SHINee. What these trolls do reflects on their idols as well and we don't want to stoop down to their level. 
In the words of our Diva Key, he's not aiming to be the best, but to be someone he's not ashamed to be. SHINee is not ashamed of who they are and their style, so why should the haters' words affect us? 
We know SHINee, they are legendary, talented, and ambassadors of Hallyu. Not once in the last 8 years have they asked Shawols to help them win awards, but simply to enjoy their music, so let's do exactly that, for SHINee and for our SHINee World. <3

text:
SHINee is entering their 9th year & I've been a Shawol long enough from a teen fangirl and now a fully employed lady. I'm pretty sure a lot of Shawols are around my age (*same age as Jong Hyun). SHINee will always be the 1st group that brought me to kpop in 2009. Some may say SHINee in need of 'normal concept' for once to garner more fans. I say not. I love the boys for who they are. Frankly speaking this concept looks perfectly normal because it is SHINee. Only SHINee can pull this of. They've proven everything they can do and still are slaying it. SHINee World concert tickets sold out every single time. To top that, these boys have been on SHINee World Tours for atleast 9 times not including SMTOWN Tours. 

To all Shawols, cheers! Our boys are legend and a veteran in kpop. 

p/s: Keep going with the views. I dont have time to watch, so i just let it runs on my pc with earphone plugged in.

author: @agimarodrigues6982
text:
The views are finally gradually increasing.
guys, yesterday i contacted the YouTube customer care forum to ask or rather complain about the frozen views. I later got a reply saying that YouTube recently updated their method of counting the views. read this . These are the contents of the message:
"This is absolutely normal as YouTube audits views on every video uploaded. This will cause your views to freeze and often times, decrease as YouTube discards low quality views. Low quality views include : visitors who see your video for only a couple of seconds and then leave . View counts will usually normalize after a couple of days (after upload)."
 guys we just need to watch the video till the end inorder for it to count. and  also stream as much as we can.

author: @YuKaKariyu
text: Guys, I agree that the view count is weird - but remember that a lot of other groups also just came back. A lot of Shawols that I know personally are streaming BTS's new MV over SHINee's simply b/c BTS is a newer group. Let me explain, SHINee's an older group so their fanbase has mellowed out, that is all the seasonal fans have left and all of the diehard Shawols are here to stay. BTS on the other hand is still a very young group, and still hasn't experienced that mellowing of the fanbase (EXO seems to be going through it right now). Taking all that together, a lot of my friends who are Shawols and Armys have opted to stream BTS's MV b/c they aren't worried about SHINee, they had confidence that SHINee would win so they chose to help a newer group that is still growing. Either way though...  #SaveSHINeeViewCount

text:
This is really creative to go back to the 80's style with the fashion, dance, and music sound. There's a special blend in the sound that makes it modern to this era style of pop music, and I'm like glued to the sound! 🤓 To everyone who worked hard on the music, dance, and fashion visual/music video - you've all done a great job!
To SHINee: Despite Onew not dancing most of the time in this video, I think this might be another great hit.

Tip for the future: If someone in the group is not able to dance in the video, you can balance that out by having that person be somewhat of a main focus, so that the person doesn't feel left out from 50% of the video covering dance shots.

author: @irisdalyestevez2429
text:
Everyone..please..We need to vote for our boys. We need to try our best for our boys, even if it means watching this the old school way and closing out of the tab, searching for the video, and letting it play- every single time. The gap is insane, the view count is insane. I know it is hard not to believe all of this is the result of some rigging/injustice/or something, but the best we can do is just /continue/ supporting! Here's the link: http://mwave.interest.me/mcountdown/vote/preVote

P.S: Also don't want to freak anyone out, and SHINee did just say a few days ago that this was unlikely to happen...but we have to remember that our boys are now a senior group. What happened to other senior groups when they didn't do all that great in their comebacks? They disband (can't help but think and cry about 4minute...). So please, even if all of this may just be an unnecessary fear: I'd rather sleep better at night knowing I'm helping keeping our boys afloat and continue being one of the best groups in the kpop industry, then letting them flop and regretting everything I could have done better if bad news roll around..

author: @sydneylai5592
text:
I would only be satisfied if they won Artist of the Year during award season and here's why:
1. Taemin's solo comeback was freaking awesome and shook Earth, plus he proved his dominance on Hit the Stage
2. Descendants of the Sun was a huge turning point for the kdrama industry and Onew was highly praised for his work in it
3. Jonghyun's She Is album is pure genius, and perfectly highlights his talent as a writer, producer, composer, singer, dancer, and       overall performer, plus Blue Night
4. Minho has been gaining recognition as a respectable actor and his film was (or is going to be?) in freaking Cannes Film Festival
5. Key has been designing so much of their concert and comeback concepts, and we all saw the outfits during their Japan concerts this year, they were actually life-changing, plus acting in Drinking Solo
6. Their Japan concerts and ridiculously successful Tokyo Dome concerts

So overall they've contributed so much not only to the music industry but to global entertainment as a whole, they've proved once again that they are so much more than just idols, and they've rounded out the year by being perfect and bringing back OT5 in a comeback with a concept that is in the opposite direction of what every other group is doing right now. And all in just one year.  Stan kings.

author: @TaNdy88tJiSmE
text:
Let me do a full review and state my case. When I first listened to this song, I was thinking "how would Shawol react to such a different genre of music?" From 'Misconception of Us' to 'Odd' or 'Married to the music', their music was progressing through a bit of bluesy, deep house, electro pop kind of sound. Then jumping to something like this which is vocal dominant track with syth background. This would really test the fans. And what a test it has been.

Many were debating why this music video has so few views? Why are we struggling to support them with their award winnings? There are many reasons. One could simply be the fact that this track is not one of those where you would immediately like it. Secondly, it is such a huge deviation from their usual sound that some Shawol may find it hard to fall in love with. As for me, '1 of 1' is simply not my favourite track in this album. This is my own opinion, not to say it is true. 

SHINee's musicality is undoubtedly one of the best. Their harmonies and backing vocals are all throughout this music video. Unless if you have some music background or have some form of vocal training, one may find it hard to appreciate the talent behind this music. The background music is kept simple and the same throughout this track. It is SHINee's vocals the brought colour to the track. If you really listen to it, and imagine their vocal tracks being cancelled and listen to only the background music, you will hear a mono toned music with an occasional guitar solo. Without their harmonies and vocals, this would be a very dull song.

Basically, this track or for the matter of fact, this album require multiple listening. Hwaiting!!!

author: @siyiwinniethepooh
text:
Some methods could be done to increase youtube views (not absolutely sure but better than nothing):
1. Watch the MV till the end, do not skip advertisements
2. Watch at quality at least 720p
3. Use incognito mode
4. Watch another video (eg. 1 of 1 live performances, other SHINee MVs) before watching this again
5. Use different devices (tablets, phones, computers) because multiple devices from same IP could mean multiple views
6. If you use chrome, open an incognito window, press F12, select a different device using the tab at the top, go to youtube and watch this MV, then close the window and repeat again
Perhaps we are just using the wrong method so the views are so low......Add oil and don't give up!!!

author: @jeonghantrash5736
text:
I saw some upset kpop stans👀

Omg people need to chill. Stop calling them "overrated" or "old". If you were EVER a true kpop stan, you'd know SuJu, BigBang and so many other groups that have been LEGENDS for YEARS. This is a new concept for SHINee and they are always going to be legends.

Stop calling EXO and all the other groups "kings", because they are kings in someone's eyes. All Korean groups are amazingly talented. Can you immature children go one day without comparing a group?

You don't like a group? OHHMYGOD, congrats. Keep it to yourself. It's upsetting how many butthurt stans I see down in the comments.

And about their concept, it is 90's and very pre-2000's. It's not supposed to be modern or "typical". It's different. Although it's not for everyone, just appreciate the music and you don't have to listen if you don't want to. Nobody is forcing you to comment or listen to ANYTHING. You come here of your own volition, expect some backlash.

author: @Orpheelover
text: I think what I like most about this album his how involved all of SHINee is. Like Jonghyun wrote the music of 'prism' and he, Minho and Key wrote lyrics of 'don't stop'. Minho and Key also helped with the lyrics of 'don't let me go'. Minho helped with the lyrics of 'lipstick' and 'you need me'. Onew wrote the lyrics of 'so amazing'. Taemin mentioned he worked together with the choreographer of 1of1. Like in which other group do you find the members so involved in a album? And from SM of all compagnies. And it's probably one of the best albums they did (judging that they already broke their highest sales record for day 1 by 11K). As a fan I love all their albums and songs but I can see this album is being well received.

author: @SeraphimDreamer
text: Even after 5 years of loving SHINee, I still feel the same craze whenever they have a comeback. I'm always so proud to tell everyone that no matter how many groups I go crazy for, the ones that's always in my heart is always SHINee since the moment they got me into Korean pop music. I always feel so damn happy to be a shawol, to be a part of this loving family. As much as I love SHINee, I also respect them just as much and they honestly inspire me so much with the amount of hard work they always put into everything they do. To all my fellow loving shawols, let's all continue to work hard to show our love for SHINee no matter how many times the views freeze! To everyone new, SHINee is honestly such a wonderful band and you will not regret ever joining this fandom, it's always better late than never so don't be too worried over joining the fandom this late in the game! Let's all do our best and show them our love and loyalty! (Though I won't mind Onew putting me in the prison of his smile and feeding me tofu.)

author: @shinee_love7582
text:
1. Open browser.  Does not have to be in Incognito Mode, but makes things easier.
2.  You can be logged in to Youtube or not.  It does not matter.
3.  Watch  music video.  You can search for it or use a bookmark.  Either way works.  You can watch it in any video quality.  240, 360, 480, 1080, It all works. after watching it, instead of replay or refresh, close the tab and search the mv again.
4.  After watching the whole video - this is the key:  Wait at least 4 minutes before watching it again.  If you wait 5 minutes, your chances of getting your view counted increases.  If you wait less than 4 minutes before watching the MV again, your chances of getting your view counted decreases.  It may get counted, but not likely.
5.  While waiting, you can watch another video, but it is not required; just waiting.  Watching another video like will make waiting easier and more accurate.
6.  After 10 views  clear your browser cache and cookies.  Start again.

Credits:EXOTIC_BROCOLLI
