author: @ParkBomming
text: I'm so.. proud. LOL. I love it so much when SHINee has an "old school" sound in their music. I remember when the Dream Girl album came out and had "Punch Drunk Love" like a 70s feel to it. And now they brought 90s back and I know not many people appreciate that sound anymore, but I'm one of the few that does. I think SM likes to have SHINee do this kind of throwback style a lot, and that's why I think SHINee will always be my favorite SM artist. I wonder what an Onew, Key, and Minho mini album would bring tbh. I know Jonghyun really likes bass in his R&B music, and Taemin has various genres in his music, but I wonder what kind of music Onew, Key, and Minho likes. Idk, but I'm sort of ready to hear something from Onew (aka mini album/full album.) I feel like he needs some spotlight attention, especially since he's one of the main vocals.

text: At first I thought the clothing style was just like the clothing the use for NCT U and NCT127 but oml Key at 0:16....WORK IT HUNNY YAS!!!! and it's so cool that he's an art directer now and my baby Onew is so cute and his voice in this, actually all their voices and the way the song is, it's light and refreshing and the colors are cool like they're plain blue, yellow, red and brown but the way it looks, maybe it's the camera angle, reminds me of the shows like That Girl and the colored episides of Petticoat Junction and I love it. GUYS, MY #1 GROUP SHINEE'S BACK!! My sister is gonna freak when I tell her I liked it; her bias is Jonghyun and he looks amazing with that blue suit and the red turtle neck underneath. I found this kinda funny, I just realized, seeing it again, at 3:09 Taemin's wearing a yellow suit and a blue turtle neck, Jonghyun's wearing a blue suit and a red turtle neck, Onew's wearing a red suit and a brown shirt and Key is wearing a brown suit. Then there's Minho, with that pinstripe suit and the red button up and the gray-ish blonde hair, lookin like a pimp XD. But Taemin and Onew look like a ketchup and mustard bottle lmao. Like, if I was surrounded by that many ladies, I...well, they are so gorgeous and they have this classy-ness to them, like even they're outfits are cute.

author: @deffy57
text:
I used to be really into SHINee back in 2010-2013, they where basically my life. I would watch them live & buy their stuff, I even cried when they won artist of the year in 2013, that was such a good year for them.
Then high school happened, and I kinda forgot about the whole k-pop world. However, this randomly popped out on my home page, and i'm so glad it did.
I'm remembering all those fangirl feels right now, I still love these 5 boys just like I used to. My shawol spirit is still there & it hasn't changed a single bit. I'm definitely coming back to support them in their comeback❤️
Once a shawol, always a shawol~

author: @OddWeird461
text:
After reading the comments I have to assume that very few of the supposed SHINee fans actually paid attention to anything about this comeback until the MV was released.  It's a 90s throwback concept.  Everything about it is related to the 90s or 80s, including the simple music video and the white background, their clothing, etc.  

If you have issues with any of it, take it up with Key, who I'm sure did all the clothing concepts and maybe even the mv, because he's supposedly now one of SM's art directors.  Take it up with all of them, because they all had something to do w/ the album. 

I actually love it, because I'm older than most of you. I'm also open to new things as well.  SHINee already did EDM, the 70s, trap, electronica, etc. I love that SHINee is willing to experiment and do new things.  I'm sure I'll see other kpop groups copying this concept pretty soon, and when I do, I'll be sure not to go to their videos and complain about how boring they are, since I'll understand wtf is going on.

Edit to add- Going back to my earlier statement about not paying attention: ONEW HURT HIS ANKLE DURING THEIR LAST CONCERTS. That's why he's sitting in the mv. He's better now.

It's simply a new concept, every artist does this! EXO's Lotto was nearly entirely different from EXO's usual style, if they can try something new why can't SHINee? SHINee are kings they have some amazing songs and dances out there, plus each of them have their individual solo activities whether it be acting, singing or even variety shows! Experimenting is included in being an artist, they can't stick to the same things everytime otherwise you'll all get bored and complain. I love SHINee for trying something new and out of their comfort zone!! Well done to them!!!

author: @jjongmander7586
text:
I RESPECT ALL OF YOUR OPINIONS, BUT FOR ME THIS COMEBACK IS ONE OF A KIND!!! ಥ⌣ಥ

I am really amazed how SHINee used an 80s or 90s concept for this comeback and not use what's trending in this generation, which is EDM or Electronic Dance Music. For me, that's a brave and heroic thing to do. I think SHINee wants to make us remember how KPOP started in the past even before they debuted. I also think this is a tribute to the legendary groups who opened Hallyu or spread KPOP internationally. I am really proud of SHINee for doing this kind of stuff and even though a lot of people think their concept is outdated, I STILL THINK THIS COMEBACK IS AWESOME ❤❤❤ 'cause I'm a Shawol, what can I do? GO SHINEE GO!

text: I get it, some people don't like this kind of concept and so on.. i get your point, why is this, why is that.. but please if your going to rant very rudely you should better back off.. SHINee pulled out their best in making this comeback.. New concept, 90's style and different timeline.. Its supposed to be a reminder of the past.. of how trendy the past is.. most of you all are like.. the fuck SM, this is so boring.. blah..blah..blah.. We get it but can't you see, all of what is happening to kpop is all like dark/mystery/loud music..And I like it too but sometimes you just gotta take it slow.. And that's SHINee is!! Being different from the others.. The trend setters kings.. They've comeback, they've been working hard so instead of nagging about this piece of art... Take a look of yourself, are you worthy enough to judge this group this way?? I bet you can't even work hard as much as they do.. So just sit back and appreciate SHINee's comeback..OK?

If your not part of the fandom, don't you dare comment and compre SHINee to your bias groups, cuz SHINee aren't them, they are their own persona. This is very reminiscent of songs from 80's and 90's. I feel like Michael Jackson has been so influential to SHINee in their music, that's the feel I get from this song and this song is such a nice change from all the modern day, EDM style music. I'm not a fan of EDM but I don't mind it as long as there's good singing mixed in, though I much prefer "plainer" music that doesn't have so many electronic sounds.

I think Onew rocks this concept so well, shout out to the most underrated member please.

I love the girls in this, they are so pretty and funny to look at xD

You have the blue girls who cross their legs from side to side (Jonghyun)
The red girls who make do the torso swing movements (Onew)
Then the orange/yellow girls who keep going from laying on their sides to sitting on their bums (Taemin)
The White, grey, blue ones keep going all Vogue (Kibum)
and the other black and red girls who keep turning around (Minho)

It would look strange on it's own, but this combination makes is fun to look at.

author: @ninisoo6537
text:
I've been a fan of Shinee for 6 years now. I'm a fan of every kpop group you can think of but the group that has touched me the most has been Shinee. Their music is music that stands out to me. I'm thankful that they've been together for so many years and I hope they'll continue to grow together as a family. Shinee shows that even though there are many ups and downs, you can still make it together. To all the people who start "fandom wars" or just talk about other groups like they are trash, or bring people down for what they like, or say hurtful words, or fight meaningless fights with their friends of close ones, we should all learn something from Shinee. 
- sincerely, a Kpop fan since 2009/2010

author: @charhoang
text:
RIGHT SHINee's finally back so it's time to start streaming this MV as much as you can! here is a guide:


STEP 1: sign out of your youtube account/use an incognito tab. 

STEP 2: watch the whole video. you don't actually have to watch it - although it's better if you do just to appreciate shinee's hard work - but make sure it plays the whole way through. and make sure you're watching the official mv from smtown's official channel! 

STEP 3: replay the video. do NOT click refresh or paste the link into the address bar again. instead manually search the video by typing in 'shinee 1of1' in the search bar, or going to smtown's official channel and looking for it

STEP 4: repeat, repeat, repeat. every 5-7 watches, clear your browser cache. every 30min change your IP address; you can do this by turning data on and off if you're using mobile data or by plugging + unplugging your wifi router. 

STEP 5: the most important step - SHARE THE VIDEO. shove it in everybody's faces, make them watch it. talk about it, spread the word. and who knows? maybe they become fans of shinee too! 

TIPS ⬇
▪️ put the volume up at least half way! 
▪️ try to stream at at least 720p
▪️ make a youtube playlist, but include other shinee official videos in it too, like 1of1's teaser! 
▪️ watch short videos in between streaming the mv! youtube will look for 'real' views, so make it look like you're watching it legitimately!
